{"staticAdditionalInfo":"<p><span>Under the new European Social Fund plus, the EaSI programme becomes a strand of the ESF+, and gets a legal basis to establish national contact points (NCPs) for the EaSI strand. Many EU programmes already support contact points, focal points, support offices or similar structures operated by, on behalf, or within the national, regional and/or local authorities. Their role is to promote the programme and its results in the EU Member States and other countries participating in the programme, supporting beneficiaries and in some cases also assisting applicants in preparing proposals. </span></p>
<p>The available call budget is <strong>EUR 2 000 000</strong>.</p><p>This budget might be increased by maximum 20%.</p>
